\n<\n[1]>There's no damn chicken around anymore,\. I've dealt with it!
\n<\n[1]>Now,\. let me through!\.\. \BST[7]What a waste of time.\.\.
\n<Gate Guard>You did...\.\.\. wha-?\.\. How did you...?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Don't ask questions you don't want to hear the answer.
\n<\n[1]>Dealing with you guards is too much of a hassle.\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>So if this Cucco goes bye bye,\. the gates'll open back up,\. right?\.\.
At the guard's nod,\. the catgirl huffs,\. flicking her tail.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Guess I'll just have to wait till then.\.\. Keep up the good work or whatever,\. "sir".\.\.
\n<Gate Guard>If you're heading into the forest,\. be careful of that Cucco,\. Missus.\.\. They're real territorial even on a good day!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Nyah.\.\. Not my first time shooing away an angry bird.\.\.
Neneko waves a hand dismissively,\. turning away from the Guard.\.\. It would've been nice if they just let her walk in for once,\. but...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>It's always something...\.\.\. nya,\. whatever,\. time to figure out what to do.\.\.
Neneko approaches the main gate of End City,\. hardly paying attention to anything besides her mission.\.\.
Her stride is only stopped when a gloved hand stretches in front of her,\. getting in her way.\.\. An armored man,\. one of the guards,\. looks at her,\. stern.\.\.
\n<Gate Guard>Halt right there,\. ma'am.\.\. You can't go through here right now.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Ugh.\.\. Actually,\. I think I can,\. if you'd just let me take a few more steps,\. mister!\.\.
His gaze hardens as he doesn't relent.\.\.
\n<Gate Guard>Sorry,\. but orders are orders,\. no entry or exits permitted.\.\. You have to turn back.\.\.
The catgirl frowns,\. crossing her arms,\. a slight dissatisfied hiss escaping her.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>And why,\. exactly,\. are you blocking the gates?\.\.

\n<Gate Guard>Well,\. missy,\. I guess it's fair to tell ya.\.\. We've got reports of a Cucco loose around here.\.\. We've gotten a few attacks already and it's wandering a bit too close to the city for people's liking.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>A Cucco?\.\. You're really shutting the gates just because of some oversized bird?\.\.

\n<Gate Guard>I don't know what the thing's doing out here instead of in its own territory,\. but we've been instructed not to open the gates for anything so long as that thing's angry and hunting near it.\.\.
\n<Gate Guard>Apologies,\. missus.\.\. But orders are orders.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>But...\.\.\. I have really important business in the city,\. sir!\.\. \BST[2]It's for my family!\.\. Oh,\. please,\. won't you open it for me?\.\. *Sniffle*
Neneko lowers herself and sulks,\. widening her eyes and pouting,\. her ears flicking and tilting downwards.\.\.
The guard steps back,\. but shakes his head.\.\.

\n<Gate Guard>I'm...\.\.\. real sorry to hear that,\. Missus.\.\. But as a guard I can't do anything that'll risk the people of End City.\.\. Not t' mention we'll both get in trouble!\.\. The gate stays shut!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Ugh...\.\.\. great,\. for once I get a guard that takes his job seriously...\.\.\.
The guard salutes,\. looking rather proud of how professionally he handled the situation.\.\. Neneko just rolls her eyes and frowns,\. dropping the pitiful kitten act.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>At least this guy didn't look at me funny for my ears or anything.\.\. But I still need to get in...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Tch...\.\.\. damn cowards,\. running away at the sight of that hen...
\n<\n[1]>That's too bad~\.\. Now noone's watching after this stupid gate,\. huh?
